  "tutOrigWelcomeTitle": "Welcome to Futuristic",
  "tutOrigWelcomeBody": "You're about to play tic-tac-toe like you've never seen it. No rush — we'll discover the new rules together, step by step. Ready when you are.",
  "tutOrigNumbersTitle": "Now there are numbers",
  "tutOrigNumbersBody": "You no longer place just X or O. Instead you place valued numbers — and each one carries a power. That small change changes everything.",
  "tutOrigPlaceTitle": "Place any pawn you like",
  "tutOrigPlaceBody": "You can drop any of your pawns on an empty square. Watch — a gold pawn lands on the glowing square.",
  "tutOrigDemoplaceTitle": "Now you try",
  "tutOrigDemoplaceBody": "First pick a pawn below, then tap an empty square to place it.",
  "tutOrigCapintroTitle": "You can capture, too",
  "tutOrigCapintroBody": "Here's the fun part: you can capture your opponent's pawn. Watch — a larger gold pawn lands on theirs and takes it.",
  "tutOrigCapruleTitle": "But there's one rule",
  "tutOrigCapruleBody": "To capture a pawn, yours must have a strictly greater value. A smaller pawn can't take a larger one.",
  "tutOrigDemoeatTitle": "Now you capture",
  "tutOrigDemoeatBody": "Try to capture the opponent pawn (3) in the center. First with a small pawn — then with one that's big enough.",
  "tutOrigWinruleTitle": "How you win",
  "tutOrigWinruleBody": "Winning is still familiar: line up three of your own pawns — horizontal, vertical, or diagonal. It's the line that matters, not the values.",
  "tutOrigDemowinTitle": "Complete the line",
  "tutOrigDemowinBody": "Place a pawn on the glowing empty square and complete the right-column trio.",
  "tutOrigDemoeatwinTitle": "Capture and win at once",
  "tutOrigDemoeatwinBody": "This time your winning move also captures. Pick a pawn big enough to take the opponent's 5 in the center, place it there, and close the diagonal.",
  "tutOrigDoneTitle": "That's Original!",
  "tutOrigDoneBody": "Now you know the power of numbers, capturing, and winning. Try it in a real game — be the one who wins.",
  "tutBonWelcomeTitle": "Welcome to Bonanza",
  "tutBonWelcomeBody": "This is where luck joins the game. We'll uncover this mode's twist together in a few turns — don't worry, the fun part is close.",
  "tutBonOriginalTitle": "First, the basics",
  "tutBonOriginalBody": "You place pawns and win by lining up three of yours — just like in Original. If you haven't learned that yet, drop by there first.",
  "tutBonHookTitle": "What if…",
  "tutBonHookBody": "what if you held some of your opponent's pawns from the very start? 🙂 That's exactly what Bonanza does.",
  "tutBonRandomTitle": "It all starts with a number",
  "tutBonRandomBody": "In Bonanza a random number is drawn at the start of every game. It decides how many of your own pawns you'll hold.",
  "tutBonLuckTitle": "The rest are the opponent's",
  "tutBonLuckBody": "The rest of your pawns come in your opponent's color. If you're lucky enough, you could play almost the whole game with the opponent's pawns.",
  "tutBonDealTitle": "Let's see what you got",
  "tutBonDealBody": "This game the number is 4: 4 of your own pawns (gold) and 2 opponent pawns (bordeaux). Here's your hand.",
  "tutBonDemowinTitle": "Win with your own pawn",
  "tutBonDemowinBody": "Pick one of your gold pawns and complete the bottom-row trio by placing it on the glowing square.",
  "tutBonWarningTitle": "But one day your pawns run out",
  "tutBonWarningBody": "When your gold pawns run out, only the opponent's remain in your hand. And placing those… can help your opponent.",
  "tutBonDemoloseTitle": "A forced move",
  "tutBonDemoloseBody": "Only opponent pawns are left in your hand and you must place one on an empty square. But look — wherever you place it, you hand your opponent a line.",
  "tutBonDoneTitle": "That's Bonanza!",
  "tutBonDoneBody": "Bonanza is where luck meets strategy. Sometimes the opponent's pawns smile on you, sometimes they bite. Give it a go — is luck on your side?",
